Yea, that Nason stuff is one step below Dulux---and that is the lowest
of all the  enamel's I can think of---this is Dupont's answer to Farm
and Fleet enamel---cheap farm tractor, johnny one coat, enamel--not a
wise selection of paint------

I would like to see a bus properly refinished in 40 hour's------no way.

A Mack truck, with no body work whatsoever  book time is 48
hour's----and a bus has almost double the surface area----

Later,

Terry


 
