From: bugnut1(-at-)prodigy.net (bugnut1) Date: Sun, Mar 17, 2002, 11:43am
(CST-2) To: type2(-at-)type2.com Subject: [T2] painting 
I am in the process of painting my newly aquired 77 Westy in my single
car garage. 
I am using two stage nason brand paint. A cheaper offspring of dupont.
This bus was in very nice shape. 
Only a few dents to fix and the normal stone chips. Original paint so
there is only one coat on it to remove. 
I am goint to have about 350.00 in materials and about 40 hours worth of
work. Maybe a little more. 
If you are using two stage you really dont need a booth. It`s very
fogiving. A little wet sanding and buffing and you would be surprised at
what you can do yourself. 
Thanks,
Dave Parsons
(77 Westy) Gertrude 
